<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01 Transitional//EN">
<html>
<head>
<title>Help: Adding an item to the catalog</title>
<meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=iso-8859-1">
<link href="../style.css" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css">
</head>

<body>
<p class="titlebold">Adding an item to the catalog</p>
<p class="text">Open the site you want to edit and select  Items. Click on
  New Item... in the submenu. Enter a name for your new item and select an item
  or template to base your new item on. Your new item will appear in your items
  list.</p>
<p class="text"><em>Note: If there are more than 20 items on the order site,
    new items may appear on a different page than is selected.</em></p>
</body>
</html>
